'''Pølser''' is the [[Danish language|Danish]] word for [[sausage]] (Plural, sg. Pølse). Visiters to [[Denmark]] immediately learn this word, for '''pølser''' are a very important part of everyday culture in Denmark and an ingrediant in the national [[hot dog]].

One is presented with a choice with the Danish hot dog: whether one wants ''ristet pølse'' or ''kogt pølse''. The first is a [[Bratwurst]] (''ristet'' means ''roasted'') and the second a type of sausage that has precooked and preprocessed meat that is cooked a second time. 

The most noticeable aspect of the ''Pølser'' is that in Denmark they often contain a traditional red dye (''rød pølse'').

